FBIS3-11734 "drlat058_c_94009" FBIS-LAT-94-058 Document Type:Daily Report 25 Mar 1994 MEXICO National Mourning Continues 25 Mar; Banks To Open PA2503045694 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network in Spanish 0330 GMT 25 Mar 94 PA2503045694 Mexico City Canal 13 Television Azteca Network in Spanish 0330 GMT 25 Mar 94 Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [From the "Events" newscast] [Text] President Carlos Salinas de Gortari issued an order stating that the national flag will fly at half mast on Friday [25 March] as a sign of national mourning. This means that the national mourning, which had been established for Thursday, will continue tomorrow. The order states that the measure is in keeping with the deep indignation and rejection with which Mexican society has rejected the assassination of Luis Donaldo Colosio, presidential candidate for the Institutional Revolutionary Party. The order will be published in DIARIO OFFICIAL on Friday. The decision to prolong the national mourning until tomorrow, however, does not imply the suspension of labor duties. The Finance and Public Credit Secretariat announced that all financial operations will resume tomorrow. This is important information bearing in mind that the national mourning will continue tomorrow. Financial sector operations will resume tomorrow. Banks and the Mexican Stock Exchange will resume their normal activities, according to the Mexican Bank Association.
